Interested readers are strongly recommended to consult the original document via the source URL to view the numerous charts and illustrations which accompany the text and condense the large volume of information.

The Southern hemisphere winter epidemic is now over, and the Northern hemisphere winter epidemic is only just beginning to develop. Respiratory syncytial virus is now a decreasing cause of influenza-like illness in both hemispheres.

No novel influenza viruses have so far made an appearance, and the new recommended northern hemisphere vaccine is likely to be effective.

The avian-derived H5N1 and H7N9 influenza viruses remain sporadic or absent with H7N9 restricted to South China. The expected winter outbreak of seasonal influenza in Southern China has yet to make its appearance. - Mod.CP]
